# Pet-Owner (holder) wallet - environment.
#
# The wallet has no backend of its own. It only needs to know the URL of a prover-service it trusts
# to turn a credential + consent into a Groth16 proof (the same "owner's own prover" model the native
# 32-bit fallback uses). The verifier host comes from the link/QR the owner scans, not from here.

# The owner's trusted prover-service base URL (POST /prove-verification).
# demo-up.sh runs one at :41875; tunnel it for a phone/remote demo.
VITE_OWNER_PROVER_URL=http://localhost:41875
